Definition.WordDefinition: Patent \Pat"ent\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Patented}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Patenting}.] To grant by patent; to make the subject of a patent; to secure or protect by patent; as, to patent an invention; to patent public lands. [1913 Webster]
patented adj : (of devices and processes) protected by patent; "they are patented inventions"
